2.  What are the important pillars in OOP?

Encapsulation: Bundling data and methods, restricting access to certain parts.
Abstraction: Showing only what is necessary
Inheritance: Parent-child relationshi. Inheriting properties and methods from a parent class.
Polymorphism:  Object can act differently under different conditions

